	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I have a level 25 ranger, and a level 24 Druid.  I started playing the Druid when I became bored of the constant chore of walking from zone to zone.<BR>
<BR>
I managed to level to 14 in 3 days, and in playing time I hit level 20 in just over 1 day.  A druid is by far the most overpowered class in the game, and can therefore easily adapt to most environments.<BR>
<BR>
We are great in groups, as either the blaster, the medic, the buffer, the tracker/teleporter or as a temporary tank and melee fighter.  Soloing, and the name Kite is much associated to the Druid, as we can Sow, Snare and DoT.  Probably one of the most lethal and successful killing combinations in EQ.<BR>
<BR>
If you want to level as I did, and I am afraid it is a powerplaying method, follow these steps.  <BR>
<BR>
Make a woodelf Druid, and level to 4 killing the usual bats, wasps and pawns.  I prefer not to kill Wolves, just doesn't feel right.<BR>
<BR>
At level 5 or 6 head to Butcherblock and kill giant spiders to level to 6 or 7.  Then kill Dwarf Skeletons at the druid circle.  This will get you to level 10.<BR>
<BR>
At 10 go to Steamfont and kill Ebon Drakes, Harpies, Earth Elementals and the occasional wandering Mino Slaver.  This will get you to level 14 (Ward summoned is excellent against the elementals in SF).<BR>
<BR>
At 14, you start to Kite.  You now have SoW and your first DoT.  Go to West Karana, and group with another Druid.  Using the ability to out run and kill, you can swap the lure between each other until its dead.  Kill Scarecrows on the Cornfields here.  At level 17, solo them to level 22.<BR>
<BR>
At 22, go to East Karana and kill Crag Spiders.  The Dot, Lightning and Sow will work nicely on them.  Dont melee them as they poison bad<BR>
<BR>
At level 27, head to Aviak Village and Solo Avocets.  This will get you to level 32, and open the game up for you.  Have fun, and if ya see me around on Fennin Ro... say Hi... :)<BR>
<BR>
Kyte Starlyte<BR>
Officer of the Blue Dragons<BR>
The world server of Fennin Ro<BR>
Somewhere in Norrath.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
