				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				About the above post. I play a level 40 Druid on Fennin Ro and I must say Druids are most definatly not the most powerful class. First of all Druids dont even start to become good until level 14. That is when they get their first real Damage over Time spell.  They are still very ineffective until level 19. Then they become more effective in groups becuase they can actually deal out some decent damage. <BR>
<BR>
The Druid class is very balanced out. Considering we are a Priest class but cannot dish out as much damage as mages and our spells are a lot less mana efficient. <BR>
<BR>
I would recommend going to the Aviak House at level 22 and binding at the zone to lake Rathe. Unrest is also the best for level 23-29.<BR>
<BR>
On any kiting issue, Anything past level 35 solo will tear you into bits. For example a level 35 mob will often hit for over 150 damage a round. A level 35 guard will max out at 214 damage or so a round.  At level 40 the deal is either group or kite guards or Giants solo.
