			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I agree with Xanthus, Druids are very well balanced we do it all but none better then anyone else. We can kite easier in the teens but eventualy Shaman have us out DoTed. We Teleport sooner but only by one level. Our only unique ability is WolfForm spells(yes Rangers get this at lvl49, they are druid/warrior highbrids afterall). Nice but not outstanding. Were adaptable to most any zone. A druid in the right hands is most formidable, but isn't any class in the &quot;right hands&quot;<BR>
<BR>
As for Kiting. North Karna at 14 becuase you can kite Griffawns, Borers and Pincers. There always plenty to go around at this level. You can kit Scythes at level 16ish and at level 20 to 21 you can kite Griffennes. Fennes are rare beucase there ver popular right now. At 22 you can head to SouthKarana and hunt Rooks and harriers then at 24 you can start some adovcates these will last till 28 to 29 where Griffons(Griffins) are now possible but only the weaker ones. Also at level 29 you can start to group kite HillGiants.<BR>
<BR>
I am now lvl 30 and still find some HGs and Griffons impossible due to higher then 50% resists. Also these are all Red to me where I do get great XP but suffer from long kite times. The Griffons require the Snare, DoT, run Med run Med run Snare DoT again  method. This is hard and requies much practice. I did this with Harriers and Advocates and Found I could kite 3 to 4 with no downtime in between. I can Kite two lower but red Griffons back to back assuming I can find them this quick. This is assuming you have been buying the all important Wisdom buffing items. Mine is 154 and this plays a large factor by lvl30. This is 39points from what I started with giving me 240 more mana at lvl30 then I would have with out the items.<BR>
<BR>
Also Qeynos Guards can be done at level 19 up but faction hits can make life hard. At Level 30 I double team NPC Dwarves(not guard) in ButcherBlock. I have killed over 60easy and still the Dwarf Guards Love my Halfling Druid. I am not willing to go into Kaladim anymore but I do not have a need to.<BR>
<BR>
This is not complete and not suited for everyone. Its from my expierence and there were multiple Deaths involved to learn what I was capable of doing and when. As with any class you play Surviving gives you game expierence, death gives you time to learn what you did wrong giving you actual expierence. I consider my self an expert Solo and Paired Kiter if anyone wishes for a guide on how I recomend plz let me know here and I will try to type one up.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
