	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				HALFLING DRUIDS may make use of Scarab Armor made by Vacto in the fighter's guild in  the dwarven city of Kaladim. It is relatively cheap since a player can loot the required components from ... well Scarabs. The giant Scarabs around Freeport give the Pristine Giant Scarab Carapice needed for the Breastplate ( you can find at merchants in the area for about 1PP, as they are sold by players) the rest of the components can be found on the worker scarabs and Giant Scarabs in the Butcherblock Mountains. See Vacto and ask... &quot;What about Scarab Breastplate?&quot; &quot;What about Scarab Helm?&quot; and you will get the list of components and cost for their making. This armor is a very green color and functions like plate.  Breastplate is AC 8, +1 STA, -1DEX. Helm is AC 4, -1 CHR.<BR>
I have been mistaken for Cleric often and even high level characters ask me where I got my armor. Good Fortune all!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
